         arithmetic (write - read > depth = lapped). Also critical
         for noisy transports (wireless, powerline) — corrupted
         record = skip, no retransmission cascade. Fixed-size records
         give instant reframing after noise bursts.

  block: check fill before writing. If full, spin until reader drains.
         2-3 extra bonds in the writer walk. For persistence (disk).

  kick:  dissolved into drop. Reader always knows if it got lapped
         from cursor arithmetic. No separate field needed.

The intent lives in the walk, not the metadata. A realtime writer
(audio, keyboard) uses drop (just writes). A persistence writer
(disk journal) uses block (checks fill first). Same loop, different
walk. The header stays clean — 6 fields, nothing behavioral.

