NVMe DISCOVERY
===============

Same pattern as VESA: MBR discovers in 16-bit BIOS, stores at
known address, genesis reads it.

MBR (16-bit): try 2-3 known PCI slots for NVMe class code.
Read BAR0. Store at 0x9200 (next to VESA FB at 0x9100).
Genesis reads BAR address (non-local, like FB address).

Alternative: targeted PCI config reads from walks.
  port_write(0xCF8, slot_addr) → port_read(0xCFC) → test
  2 bonds per slot. 3-4 slots max. Not a 256-slot scan.


